cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.FL, cs.SE

The paper deals with probabilistic reasoning and verification of randomized programs, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new probabilistic model of the logic of bunched implications (BI), which is a logic of assertions in separation logic. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper introduces a program logic based on the assertions in separation logic. 

cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another likely category as the paper demonstrates the verification of security properties of several cryptographic constructions. 

cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with formal reasoning about collections of random samples. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a new verification method for randomized programs.
